Ivory TUSKS a shipping container was seized in Singapore four years carrying more than SIX tons of elephant ivory conservation and law enforcement agencies realized that they had intercepted the largest shipment of the contraband material since its international trade was banned.
Zambia Friday denied that it has submitted a proposal to the Convention on International Trade in Endangered Species of Wild Fauna and Flora (CITES) for the sale of its ivory.
The UN agency regulating the trade in endangered species, , urged African states to overcome their deepening divide over a ban on the ivory trade and elephant conservation.
